<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="852" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d852">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.01/9–1644: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at
                                    Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T19:00:00+02:00">September 16, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received September 16—2:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>191. Legtel 190, September 15, 6 p.m. Foreign Minister informed me
                                that at meeting of Lebanese Cabinet last evening decision was taken
                                to refuse to enter into any treaty negotiations with the French. He
                                understood that Syrian Cabinet was to meet today to take similar
                                decision.</p>
                            <p>Spears has just sent me word that Lebanese decision has been formally
                                communicated to him.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Caserta.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>